        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Oxygen (O ) Emergency Procedure"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 3
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "In the event of oxygen supply being unable to meet the demand the following will happen."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 4
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "A sudden drop in pressure will set off local oxygen alarms, if this is a site wide issue then the sounder at the nurses station will alarm."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 5
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 1.0,
                "text": "Actions to take to avoid the compromise of the oxygen (O) system.  Clinical: Medical and Nursing responsibilities"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 6
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Site Director of Operations to make a decision if hospital site to close to all admissions."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 7
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "sequence_num": 8,
            "data": {
                "url": "MSESOP-21023 Oxygen emergency SOP.001.png"
            }
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Site Medical or Site Nursing Director to decide with immediate effect target saturations to"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 9
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "sequence_num": 10,
            "data": {
                "url": "MSESOP-21023 Oxygen emergency SOP.002.png"
            }
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "drop to 85% for all patients."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 11
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Clinicians and senior nursing staff to walk all wards and review every patient on oxygen (if"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 12
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "sequence_num": 13,
            "data": {
                "url": "MSESOP-21023 Oxygen emergency SOP.003.png"
            }
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "out of hours consultants to be called in)."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 14
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Oxygen to be provided to the sickest patients only.  ITU patients to be transferred out."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 15
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "sequence_num": 16,
            "data": {
                "url": "MSESOP-21023 Oxygen emergency SOP.004.png"
            }
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 2.0,
                "text": "Estates responsibilities"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 17
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Under these circumstances the standby manifold will be automatically be brought into use"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 18
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "sequence_num": 19,
            "data": {
                "url": "MSESOP-21023 Oxygen emergency SOP.006.png"
            }
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "and should be continuously monitored to ensure the oxygen supply to the hospital site is maintained."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 20
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Contact BOC emergency number 0800 222 888 or 0800111333 as a secondary back up"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 21
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "sequence_num": 22,
            "data": {
                "url": "MSESOP-21023 Oxygen emergency SOP.007.png"
            }
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "number."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 23
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Ensure that the state of emergency situation is stressed as critical and request that a BOC"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 24
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "sequence_num": 25,
            "data": {
                "url": "MSESOP-21023 Oxygen emergency SOP.008.png"
            }
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "service engineer is sent to the hospital urgently."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 26
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Continue to replenish the standby manifold cylinders to ensure continuation of the oxygen"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 27
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "sequence_num": 28,
            "data": {
                "url": "MSESOP-21023 Oxygen emergency SOP.009.png"
            }
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "supply."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 29
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Arrange with site pharmacy the urgent delivery of additional cylinders."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 30
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "sequence_num": 31,
            "data": {
                "url": "MSESOP-21023 Oxygen emergency SOP.010.png"
            }
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Contact East of England Ambulance service for urgent oxygen on support number 01245"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 32
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "sequence_num": 33,
            "data": {
                "url": "MSESOP-21023 Oxygen emergency SOP.011.png"
            }
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 1.0,
                "text": "Supply W cylinders to the wards according to the site ward priority list, see Appendix"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 34
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "sequence_num": 35,
            "data": {
                "url": "MSESOP-21023 Oxygen emergency SOP.012.png"
            }
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 3.0,
                "text": "Oxygen supply monitoring process"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 36
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 2.0,
                "text": "There are trigger points in place for the level of demand on the O supply as very high"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 37
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "sequence_num": 38,
            "data": {
                "url": "MSESOP-21023 Oxygen emergency SOP.013.png"
            }
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "demand over a sustained period has the potential to cause catastrophic damage to the system."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 39
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 2.0,
                "text": "There is remote telemetry available on the O demand which shows demand minute-by-"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 40
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "sequence_num": 41,
            "data": {
