        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Estates will de-ice the evaporator and take a reading of the demand on the system. This"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 46
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "sequence_num": 47,
            "data": {
                "url": "MSESOP-21023 Oxygen emergency SOP.015.png"
            }
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "reading will be reported by estates to the clinical site team and nursing controller if applicable."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 48
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "The triggers and actions below are based on the estates advice on trigger points for overall"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 49
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "sequence_num": 50,
            "data": {
                "url": "MSESOP-21023 Oxygen emergency SOP.016.png"
            }
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 2.0,
                "text": "demand. The demand figure is based on either a single reading direct from the O store by estates, or on a 30 minute average demand figure from the remote telemetry."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 51
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "***Procedure continues on next page***"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 52
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Table 2: Alert and Response"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 53
        },
        {
            "type": "table",
            "sequence_num": 54,
            "data": {
                "num_rows": 10,
                "num_cols": 1,
                "table_items": [
                    {
                        "text": "Demand (litres / minute)"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Alert Level And Response"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Less than 1,900"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Level 0 \u2013 no escalation Demand is less than 75% of planned capacity. No action required"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "1,900 to 2,250"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Level 1 \u2013 Green escalation Demand is between 75% and 90% of planned capacity. Action \u2013 Inform Clinical Site team / Hospital Out of hours (HOO) for"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "forward planning and liaison with emergency planning officer"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "2,250 to 2,400"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Level 2 \u2013 Amber escalation Demand is between 90% and 100% of planned capacity. Action \u2013 HOO team to undertake a virtual O2 round to:"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "identify from nerve centre or equivalent patients on O2 and contact wards to review SATS and wean patients above target range 88- 92% identify patients on less than 5 litres of O2 and ensure all are on - concentrators Virtual O2 rounds to be repeated 2 hourly if O2 remains in amber status continually. Action \u2013 Clinical site team to put in place O2 monitoring via remote"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "telemetry every 30 minutes. Inform Site Director of Operations & SLT in hours / SMOC and Exec on call out of hours. Consider declaration of internal critical incident"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Over 2,400"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Level 3 \u2013 Red escalation Demand is over 100% of planned capacity. If based on single reading from estates: Action \u2013 Clinical site team to immediately review remote telemetry and"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "establish escalation level based upon 30 minute average demand. If based on 30 minute average via remote telemetry: Action \u2013 Clinical site team to inform Site Director of Operations & SLT in"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "hours / SMOC and Exec on call out of hours Consider declaration of Critical / major incident dependent on the extent and impact Instigate business continuity by the reduction of oxygen use by adjusting oxygen demand by patients, and the use of oxygen concentrators Any incident can be either stepped up or down following review of situation and what effects the lack of supply is having on patient care and if this is causing a risk to life"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 2.0,
                "text": "Note \u2013 the monitoring system in place on the main O tank will also alert estates management if demand exceeds the green, amber, red trigger points above."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 55
